SIMPLE: thistly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thistly
<hw>This"tly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Overgrown
with thistles; <as>as, <ex>thistly</ex> ground</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: Resembling a thistle or thistles; sharp;
pricking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In such a world, so thorny, and where none⟦br⟧
Finds happiness unblighted, or, if found,⟦br⟧
Without some <qex>thistly</qex> sorrow at its side.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thither</ent>⟦br⟧
